name: multiplexed sequencing library
description: a multiplexed library is a material entity which is the output of a library preparation process that uses a ligation step to attach a unique multiplexing sequence identifier to a specific sample, then mixes several such tagged samples prior to the library amplification process proper. A multiplexed library allows the sequencing of several samples in one sequencing run.

name: material sample
description: A material entity that has the material sample role
